The Wi-Fi Talking Robot is an intelligent robotic system that can communicate with users through voice messages and be controlled over a Wi-Fi network. The robot receives commands wirelessly from a smartphone, computer, or web application and responds by performing actions such as moving, speaking predefined messages, or providing status information.
The system typically uses a Wi-Fi-enabled microcontroller such as the ESP8266 , along with motors, a speaker, and other electronic components. Through wireless communication, users can remotely control the robot and interact with it in real time





